  Adaon says, "Ah, so ye be wantin' to know about the bards, eh?  
Well, there be no one better t' ask than me.
  "As ye ken, bards be entertainers o' the highest degree for the most 
part, but that be hardly all of our skills.  We are also wanderers, and 
seekers o' knowledge.  A bard is an independent thinker:  we're not 
much given to >politics<, we value our independence too much.
  "As far as performin' goes, it helps t' be versatile.  Ye never know 
who ye may have in y'r audience!  Most o' the bards that come 
through here learn some >music< craft.  After all, the >lute< be our 
symbol!  We have other >talents< besides this, o' course.
  "Ye may have seen bards walkin' about with some grandiose titles.  
Well, that be part of our heritage, from the elder days when we had 
a stricter, more formal >rank< scale.  The bards were divided into 
''colleges'' that did nae associate with one another.  If ye ask me, I 
much prefer the camaraderie we have nowadays.  This is the 
friendliest guild ye can ask for.
  "We bards dabble in >magic< a wee bit as well, but by no means are 
we masters of the art!  We know enough for some tricks...>magic< is a 
tool for entertainment, though a bard is nae a bard if he's not 
imaginative!  Some of our lads and lasses come up with the most 
interesting uses for those spells.  We're not really fighters, either, but 
a bard can hold his own in the >fighting< department.  Most o' our 
skills deal wi' our relations wi' others.  The friendliness, persuasion, 
wit, and charm ye develop as a bard are your greatest allies."
  Adaon leans back then and says, "If ye be havin' any further 
questions, just ''ask about >topic<'' and I'll try t' help ye."
